<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Princedale in black with Pounds 0.39m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PRINCEDALE Group, the USM-quoted marketing and design agency, stayed in the
black in the second half to record its first annual profit since 1988.
In the year ended September 30 1992 the group turned in a pre-tax profit of
Pounds 389,000, against a loss of Pounds 431,000. Mr Stephen Bennett,
chairman, described that as encouraging particularly as the market place was
difficult.
All three remaining operating units made a positive contribution. Turnover
fell from Pounds 15.3m to Pounds 12.8m because of the sale of companies.
There were exceptional charges of Pounds 163,000 (Pounds 116,000) and a
significantly reduced net interest payable of Pounds 68,000 (Pounds
192,000).
Earnings per share were 0.08p (losses 0.11p).
</TEXT>
