<HEADLINE>
FT  26 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Templeton Emerging net asset value lifted
3.4%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TEMPLETON Emerging Markets Investment Trust, the specialist fund investing
in markets such as Brazil and the Philippines, increased its fully diluted
net asset value by 3.4 per cent in the first half of its financial year.
At October 31, its value per share was 214.23p, compared with 207.2p on
April 30. The trust was launched in June 1989 and produced the fifth best
share price performance of all investment trusts, according to Micropal,
over the three years to January 1.
The trust had investments in 157 companies operating in 13 markets at the
end of October. It hopes to launch a savings scheme for small investors this
year.
In accordance with policy, the trust is not paying an interim dividend. The
shares fell 1p to 222p yesterday.
</TEXT>
