I certainly did say that it would take 25 years to ensure parity between men
and women at work, but the 25 years I referred to was a forecast I had made
in 1975, when I was deputy chairman of the Equal Opportunities Commission.
This forecast, as you will appreciate, brings us up to the year 2000, which
